items.text:
Statisten gesucht!

Für eine Musical Show am Samstag, 21. März 2026 im Kurhaus Bad Herrenalb werden Statisten im Alter von 16 - 99 gesucht.

Die Statisterie wird mit kleinen Schauspieleinlagen, sowie Bewegungssequenzen in die Produktion integriert sein.

Gezeigt werden Ausschnitte aus Tanz der Vampire, König der Löwen, Mamma Mia, Aladdin, The Greatest Showman, Grease u.v.m.

Die Proben finden 1x wöchentlich in Bad Herrenalb bei Karlsruhe statt.

Die Leitung des Showprojekts hat Sandra Maria Germann, die das Musical Ensemble Dance Charisma leitet und seit vielen Jahren national und international als Musicaldarstellerin, Schauspielerin und Choreographin tätig ist.

Wir freuen uns auf rege Teilnahme von ambitionierten Schauspielern und Tänzern (m/w/d).

Infos & Anmeldung unter 0176 - 39 61 45 60 oder info@dance-charisma.de

 (c) Bernd Hentschel

**WARSZAWA**!! 

**10 października**

film fabularny

Na kolejne dni filmu JAN BO i już jedne z ostatnich szukam Statystów jak poniżej. Przeczytajcie proszę uważnie wytyczne charakteryzacji.

**10 PAŹDZIERNIKA (piątek):**

MŁODZIEŻ NA PRÓBIE MUZYCZNEJ 18-25 LAT - jedna scena, wnętrze. **MĘŻCZYŹNI**. Stawka: 120 zł gotówka po planie

brak tatuaży w widocznych miejscach, bez tuneli w uszach

kolczyki w nosie, brwiach czy wardze trzeba wyjąć na zdjęcia, bez wygolonych boków i bez włosów ścinanych maszynką, bez zarostów od barbera

długie włosy super

łysi panowie niestety odpadają

**ZGŁOSZENIA**

Poproszę na adres: dominika@podtytulem.pl

W tytule: JB + 10

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość + wymiary: wzrost, klatka, pas, biodra, rozmiar ubrania i buta

W załączniku: ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI: tylko z dnia zgłoszenia.

Portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy.

Panowie - dodatkowo zdjęcie z profilu

items.text:
**K-POP DANCER CASTING CALL!** ✨

We’re on the lookout for a **charismatic, high-energy dancer** with a strong passion for **K-pop culture** to bring the stage to life at an exciting upcoming event at one of our family friendly holiday parks! 

📅 **Dates needed**: Tuesday 28th & Wednesday 29th October
📍 **Location**: Lincolnshire, Accommodation provided
💷 **Pay**: £200 per day (Freelance/Temporary Contract)

**What we’re looking for:**
A confident performer with sharp choreography skills, stage presence, and the ability to get a crowd hyped! You’ll be lip-syncing and dancing to K-pop hits - solo or as part of a group - and leading a fun daytime meet & greet and dance experience.

**Key responsibilities:**
• Perform choreographed K-pop routines (lip-sync performance)
• Lead a short beginner-friendly K-pop dance class
• Interact with guests and create unforgettable moments

📧 **To apply:**
Send your **dance reel or performance video** + **social media links** to **[casting@awayresorts.co.uk](mailto:casting@awayresorts.co.uk)**

📌 Applicants must have the right to work in the UK.

Tag a friend who lives for K-pop and would love this gig! 💥

sharedPost.text:
Film zostanie wysłany na ogolnolicealny Fresh Form film festiwal, sa dwie reżyserki, w tym ja, z małym doświadczeniem ale wielkim zapałem. Mamy kamerę i stroje. Nie jest to płatne, można powiedzieć hobbistyczne, ale na pewno będzie to ciekawa przygoda. Okolice Warszawy, Piaseczna. Dni nagrywek są elastyczne 

Film jest obyczajowy, opowiada o grupie nastolatków zmagających się z problemami w rodzinie, z używkami i chorobą. Film opiera się na scenach rozmów, drogi i ‚gonitwy’. jest bardzo emocjonalny i pełen pasji.

Fajnie jakby zgłoszeni mieli styl bliski alternatywnemu, rockowemu (wielkim plusem byłaby umiejętność gry na gitarze) Szukamy przede wszystkim chłopaka 170-190cm z kręconymi włosami, grający rolę najlepszego przyjaciela głównego bohatera który stara się pomóc w leczeniu jego matki.

Poboczne role to postać chłopaka o podobnym wzroście, jasne proste lub falowane włosy, oraz jeszcze dwójki chłopaków, bez większych wymagań (jeden lepiej by było jakby miał długie włosy, hipisowski styl)

Naprawdę doceniam każdego chętnego, jesteśmy bardzo zaangażowane w tworzenie, a scenariusz jest naprawdę ambitny.

items.text:
**Looking for 4 actors/actresses**

Hey everyone! 
We’re looking for **4 people who’d like to act** in a **camera and directing exercise** at our film school.
No previous experience needed, just enthusiasm and a willingness to collaborate.

**What it’s about:**
We’ll be working on **short dialogue scenes**, each focused on **a specific emotion**. The exercise will explore **camera movement** and how actors and directors adapt to each other, just like in a film, but with short and experimental scenes.

The scenes can be performed in **English or German**, depending on what you feel most comfortable with.

🗓 **Date:** October 16th
🕙 **Time:** 10:00–16:00
📍 **Location:** FilmArche 

It’ll be a fun and creative day of learning and collaboration.
If you’re interested or know someone who might be, send me a message!

items.text:
CASTING CALL – Independent Short Film (LONDON)

We are casting for an upcoming student short film exploring obsession, ambition, and the dark side of the ballet world.

Production: Student film via The American University of Rome

Director: Maxine Sutton

Cinematographer: Georgia Blackson

Shooting Dates: December 12–19

ROLES

NATASHA (Lead)

Female, 18–28

Ballet-trained (advanced preferred)

Must convey vulnerability, intensity, and psychological depth

Strong acting, presence, and physical performance required

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250€ flat rate for entire production

RUDOLPH

Male, 25–40

Dance experience preferred

Embodies both beauty and cruelty — a man who inspires awe, fear, and complete submission.

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250€ flat rate for entire production

SYNOPSIS

Natasha, a talented but tormented ballerina, navigates a high-stakes audition that tests the limits of her physical and psychological endurance. As she strives for perfection under the watchful eye of the enigmatic Rudolph, the line between reality and terror begins to blur, forcing her to confront the true cost of ambition.

TO APPLY

Please complete the audition form and send it, along with a headshot, to: maxineclairesutton@gmail.com

🚨 EXTRAS CASTING CALL 🚨

We are now casting for EXTRAS in our RCM REP SCENE, where you will act as part of a crowd and gain the following:

✅ IMDb Credits
✅ Professional In Scene Stills/Photography for personal use
✅ The option for your in scene photos to be featured on our social media for promotional purposes

DISCLAMERS:
⚠️ We cast EXTRAS on a ONE TIME CAP, so please take note of this if you have worked as an extra with us before!
⚠️ This is an UNPAID opportunity 

We are FILMING 26th OCTOBER 2025 in HARROW ON THE HILL (specific location given to successful applicants) for 2-3pm

‼️ DEADLINE TO APPLY: 24th OCTOBER 2025

To apply, please use this link:

https://screenliftstudios.co.uk/crew-%26-extras#2eae2a5a-6970-49e6-b0a7-9d7b20451a88

*All fields, including headshot submission, are compulsory - showreel NOT REQUIRED to be an extra

To find out more about SCREENLIFT’s TRAINING OPPORTUNITIES FOR CAST AND CREW, please visit:

https://screenliftstudios.co.uk/train-%26-get-cast

NO CACHEMENT AREA REQUIRED FOR SUBMISSIONS/INVOLVEMENT FOR EXTRAS AND TRAINING ACTORS - we look forward to hearing from you soon ❤️

items.text:
🎭 FREE Introductory DRAMA Workshop For Young People In MANCHESTER This NOVEMBER 🎭

Join us at Red Players Academy for the FREE LAUNCH WORKSHOP of our BRAND NEW SATURDAY CLASS at our well-established and highly reputable drama school for young performers aged 9+

🌐 www.redplayersacademy.com/courses

🔴 RPA is Manchester’s elite-level drama school and talent agency – known for combining cutting-edge academic research with professional industry experience. Whether you’re just starting out or already experienced, our workshops are tailored to support every level!

🔴 We are an advanced training provider, offering advanced workshops in Acting, Drama, Movement, and Contemporary Performance. We teach all aspects of acting for both stage and screen, and are specialists in innovative and contemporary Creative Practice. 

🎬 Our students are currently appearing in:

📺 Netflix’s Adolescence
⚽ CBBC’s Jamie Johnson FC
🎭 13 Going on 30 @ Manchester Opera House
🔍 CBBC’s Odd Squad
…and more!

What you can expect at RPA:

🗓️ Weekly Saturday classes in Altrincham
🎭 Opportunity to participate in an end-of-year showcase in a theatre
🎬 Acting for stage and screen
🎓 Taught by expert practitioners with professional industry experience 
🌟 Curriculum is designed by acting coach & performance academic Lee Battle – credits include Coronation Street, Casualty, the BAFTA winning BBC drama The Street, Robin Hood, Awaydays and more
📣 Be considered to join our SPOTLIGHT-registered Young Performers Talent Agency
🎬 Project-based, intensive, industry-focused learning environment

🗓️ LAUNCHING SATURDAY 1st NOVEMBER 2025

📍Limited spaces available – sign up to your FREE introductory workshop now!

📱 07441 396970
📧 info@redplayers.co.uk
🌐 www.redplayersacademy.com

sharedPost.text:
Casting Call

Production: Mother's Ruin, by Steve Bird (Back by popular demand!)

The story so far in the life of Liverpool comedian Garry Skyner, one of Britain's first- born victims of the Thalidomide medical disaster. Steve Birds play is a moving and emotional, yet hard hitting play about the highs, lows, struggles and sheer determination of a loving Mother and her son who refused to be beaten by the Government and company that profited from this medical disaster.

We are looking for a talented female actor playing range 20-30ys, who is from Liverpool or can do a convincing accent, for the lead role of Frances, Gary's Mum.
Frances is a spirited, humourous woman, who whilst having a heart of gold, has an inner strength, is tough, and fights for her child and what is right.
If you believe you are what we are looking for please send you CV and headshot to elainestewart46@yahoo.com 

Auditions to take place on Sunday 21st September 1pm-3pm at a Liverpool venue to be disclosed on receipt of CV, and a script will be provided. 

Performances will take place at the Epstein Theatre on 27th and 28th February 2026.

You must be available for rehearsals Sundays 1pm- 4pm (in Liverpool) starting 2nd November.
*This is a profit share production

items.text:
🎬 Casting Call – Student Short Film

Production Title: Baggage

Director: Kole Jackson 

Role: Protagonist – Old Man

Requirement: Male actor in his 50s or 60s, preferably with a beard. Tall and skinny physique.

Shooting Dates: 18th – 19th September

As this is a passion-driven student short film, the role is unpaid, but catering will be provided throughout the shoot days.

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

📧 If interested, please reach out to:

Kole Jackson (Director)– kole.jackson.m@gmail.com

Ahad Khan (Assistant Director)– ahadg8@gmail.com

Looking for models in LA to submit ASAP! Register to apply ASAP at chaarmzmagazine.com/talentsignup for the following:

Project: HIGH FASHION LIVE EVENT
Location: Los Angeles
Rate: $350 US (minus agency commissions)
Union: Non-Union 
Audition Type: Self Tape/ Virtual
Stand-In | Any Gender | 20 - 40 | Any Ethnic Appearance

Project Synopsis: We are looking for skilled character actors to be apart of a Live Fashion Event in LA. Please see each roles for specifics. This is a live in person event - it will be live streamed on Youtube. All talent confirmed will be required to attend a fitting w/o 20th oct, a rehearsal day 25th Oct, and the event day 26th Oct. in L.A.
 
Register at chaarmzmagazine.com/talentsignup and put your profile link and instagram links under ‘profile link’ and also mention which role you’re applying for.

items.text:
ARE YOU AN ACTOR STUCK IN YOUR HEAD???

Yep... same. But I’ve been training with Steve Eastin and it’s honestly flipping everything upside down for me. You’ve seen this guy, he’s in like 200 movies [Catch Me If You Can, Con Air, Field of Dreams, Matchstick Men, etc.].

Not a lot of people even realize he’s teaching again. Feels like some random secret I lucked into.

What he does is just… different. Really different. Not about analyzing or breaking stuff down. It’s not gonna be for everyone but if you’re someone like me who gets trapped in overthinking, this is the kind of work that yanks you out of your head and dumps you right into the moment. If you live for those times where it feels like something else is taking over and you’re just along for the ride, this is that.

It’s rooted in Charles Conrad’s whole “choiceless awareness” thing. Basically stripping your brain of anything to hang onto and forcing you to just respond. No scene breakdowns, no making sure “beats” land. Just keeping it alive and messy and letting the work happen through you. If you’re curious, this article explains it better:

[[https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/](https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/)](https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/something-think-64356/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Class is super bare bones. Sit across, cold read, memorize, toss it, repeat. Just working the muscle of not thinking. Everything’s filmed so you’re used to being on camera too.

And the wild part, Conrad literally handpicked Steve to carry this forward. He taught for decades, everyone in casting knew his people, then he retired. And now he just randomly opened these tiny classes at his house. They’re small, intimate, and honestly feel like something that shouldn’t still exist.

If this even slightly calls to you, it’s a rare shot.

Classes here:

[[https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/)](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Hi everyone! 🫶🏻

I’m Bogi, Casting Manager at Deep Creative Collective (https://www.tiktok.com/@thedeepcc) based in Budapest. We create fun and viral content for brands on TikTok, Instagram, and Google.

Right now, I’m looking for someone in Zagreb who could be the next host for Wolt’s video ads! 🎥
We’re searching for someone energetic, passionate and confident, who would love to appear on camera and represent cool brands.

Details:
 • Location: Zagreb
 • Work: 1 shoot day/month (6–8 hours)
 • Content: 6 short videos per month
 • Pay: 120€ per shoot day
 • Requirements: 18-30years old MAN good English & ability to ride a bike 🚲

If this sounds like you (or someone you know), feel free to reach out – I’d love to hear from you! ✨

items.text:
Hallo👋🏻 Wir suchen für unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt hobbymäßige Schauspieler*innen (m/w/d), sowie eine Regieassistenz (m/w/d) und Drehorte für unser neues Projekt! 

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerstörerische als auch versöhnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Außerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche für das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, während Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umstände. Rache möchte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig möchte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiespältigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Auflösung: Am Ende erhält Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse über 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird überführt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Versöhnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Glück in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, düster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteriös, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet für Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gefühlen auseinandersetzen möchten. 

Das Drehbuch enthält 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erwünscht sind :)

Ziel des Projekts: Wir möchten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, darüber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Außerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, würde ich nach Möglichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestmöglichen Abschluss für die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich würde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualität hinkriegen 😊 Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges kürzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschränkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsmöglichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage würden diesmal nach Möglichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Veröffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:
Maite Fuhrmanns Leiche - Spielalter 13 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag 

Viktor Drews Leiche - Spielalter 35-40 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag 

Ludwig Cifer - Spielalter 40-50 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - Mafiaboss, intelligent, bedrohlich, ist sehr rassistisch, trans* und behindertenfeindlich, schuldbeladen, gerissen, stirbt am Ende 

Liora Lisov - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - ca. 3 Drehtage - lässt sich von Angst leiten, gerissen, hinterlistig, spielt Theater, am Anfang freundlich, aber zeigt dann ihr wahres Gesicht, stirbt am Ende 

Ben Saalfeld - Spielalter 17-18 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - hasserfüllt, rachsüchtig, genießend, ängstlich, spielt Psychospielchen mit seinen Opfern, stark, stirbt am Ende, nachdem er wichtige Erkenntnisse erhält 

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, fürsorglich, zuhörend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Zusätzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort für Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das wäre voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Schäfer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der Nähe von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pläne in die Tat umzusetzen und glücklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pläne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und möchte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler Hürden, wie Autismus, Transidentität und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Plänen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

Hallo👋🏻 Wir suchen für unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt hobbymäßige Schauspieler*innen (m/w/d), sowie eine Regieassistenz (m/w/d) und Drehorte für unser neues Projekt! 

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerstörerische als auch versöhnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Außerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche für das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, während Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umstände. Rache möchte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig möchte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiespältigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Auflösung: Am Ende erhält Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse über 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird überführt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Versöhnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Glück in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, düster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteriös, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet für Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gefühlen auseinandersetzen möchten. 

Das Drehbuch enthält 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erwünscht sind :)

Ziel des Projekts: Wir möchten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, darüber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Außerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, würde ich nach Möglichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestmöglichen Abschluss für die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich würde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualität hinkriegen 😊 Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges kürzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschränkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsmöglichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage würden diesmal nach Möglichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Veröffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:
Maite Fuhrmanns Leiche - Spielalter 13 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag 

Viktor Drews Leiche - Spielalter 35-40 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag 

Ludwig Cifer - Spielalter 40-50 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - Mafiaboss, intelligent, bedrohlich, ist sehr rassistisch, trans* und behindertenfeindlich, schuldbeladen, gerissen, stirbt am Ende 

Liora Lisov - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - ca. 3 Drehtage - lässt sich von Angst leiten, gerissen, hinterlistig, spielt Theater, am Anfang freundlich, aber zeigt dann ihr wahres Gesicht, stirbt am Ende 

Ben Saalfeld - Spielalter 17-18 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - hasserfüllt, rachsüchtig, genießend, ängstlich, spielt Psychospielchen mit seinen Opfern, stark, stirbt am Ende, nachdem er wichtige Erkenntnisse erhält 

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, fürsorglich, zuhörend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Zusätzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort für Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das wäre voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Schäfer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der Nähe von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pläne in die Tat umzusetzen und glücklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pläne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und möchte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler Hürden, wie Autismus, Transidentität und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Plänen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

**AUDITION NOTICE FROM PUTNEY THEATRE COMPANY**

**THE SEAFARER**

**by Conor McPherson**
**Sunday 26 October, 3pm**
**Monday 27 October, 7pm***

*If successful, you will be asked to attend a recall on Wednesday 29 October at 7pm

**Performances:**
**Tuesday 17 February 2026 – Saturday 21 February 2026, Putney Arts Theatre **

**AUDITION INFORMATION:**

For the audition you will be asked to perform either a selected monologue or short scene from the play. You may be asked to perform it a second time with some direction or with another auditionee.

All the characters in the play are Irish. All the characters, except for Mr Lockhart, come from Baldoyle, north of Dublin. Mr Lockhart could be from anywhere in Ireland.

When auditioning you should be able to show an ability and familiarity with an Irish accent, although we don’t expect it to be perfect at this point. Unless of course you are from North Dublin!

**Please contact the director on *****[ian@nickhernbooks.co.uk](https://www.putneyartstheatre.org.uk/mailto:%20peterpanto2025@gmail.com)*****  for audition pieces and any further information required.**

**ABOUT THE PLAY:**

A supernatural tale on a dark winter’s evening…

It’s nearly Christmas Eve and Sharky has returned to Dublin to look after his blind brother, Richard. As the two men rattle around their old house, they are joined by local layabouts Ivan and Nicky - and a stranger, new to town, the mysterious Mr Lockhart.

Over a night fuelled by alcohol and resentment, a game of cards is on the table. But the cost of losing may be higher than anyone imagines…

From Conor McPherson, award-winning author of The Weir and Girl from the North Country, comes a blackly funny, haunting tale of family and friendship, steeped in whiskey and stirred by regret and the need for redemption.

**CAST BREAKDOWN:**

Five Men aged 35-65 (ages in brackets are the possible age range for the parts).
* **Sharky**: On the wagon. A man who has lost in life and love but is struggling to be better. Trying to hold it together but lacking in the confidence he once had. (35 - 45)
* **Richard:** A big drinker. Recently blinded. A dishevelled, fetid old rogue. Irascible, childish and demanding but with a whiff of Irish charm. (50 - 65) 
* **Ivan: **A big man. An innocent, but full of anxiety.  A hard drinker who suffers from the aftereffects of his imbibing. (35 - 45)
* **Nicky: **The local wide boy. Confident cocky, always on the up and on the lookout. Thinks he’s much better than he is. (30 - 40)
* **Mr Lockhart:** Enigmatic. A different class to the other men and something of a mystery to them. Sophisticated in comparison, he is possessed of a dark and dangerous edge. (50 - 60)

“Sparkling and suspenseful… McPherson is a born yarn-spinner” Guardian

“A realistic fantasy, a wide-awake nightmare. The writing is poetic, brutal, athletic, hilarious” Sunday Times

“Conor McPherson is the heir to the great Irish tradition of absorbing tale telling” Observer

“The finest dramatist of his generation” The Telegraph 

**Please contact the director on *****[ian@nickhernbooks.co.uk](https://www.putneyartstheatre.org.uk/mailto:%20peterpanto2025@gmail.com)*****  for audition pieces and any further information required.**

**PLEASE NOTE: this is an amateur production and therefore non-paid. **

Two weeks from today, October 22 live and in person!! Mission 1 Billion meeting Wednesday, October 22, 7pm at Schmidty’s  Bar and Grill in Brookfield. Come early and stay late so we could begin on time.. Share with your filmmaker and actor friends.

Rocky Wagonhurst’s five-decade journey through the world of media is nothing short of extraordinary. He began in the 1970s as a Universal Studios tour guide and went on to appear on The Young and the Restless, star in national commercials, and play Laertes in a five-hour production of Hamlet. He was also directed by Steven Spielberg in Minority Report alongside Tom Cruise and once soared 10,000 feet above Lake Tahoe in a glider with actor Cliff Robertson. His career has spanned radio, stage, and screen, ultimately leading him behind the camera as a seasoned television executive. Currently, Rocky serves as Vice President and General Manager of The CW and My24 stations in Milwaukee, bringing his lifelong passion for storytelling and media innovation to local broadcasting. 

Mark your calendar now and we will see you then! Look for us on FB too @everyone  

ENTER  the door under the White Claw sign

Please share ! Help us spread the word this is open to the public.

items.text:
**CASTING VIDEO – MANN UM DIE 40 – HANDWERKSBIER**
## 

Sind Sie ein Mann um die 40, natürlich und kamerafreundlich?

Sie sprechen **fließend Deutsch** (Pflicht) und können sich mit unserem Team auf **Französisch oder Englisch**verständigen?

Wir suchen einen Darsteller für einen Werbedreh zur Erstellung von **Videoinhalten für die sozialen Netzwerke** einer **handwerklich gebrauten Biermarke**.

📍 **Ort**: Lausanne, Schweiz

🕐 **Dauer**: Halber Drehtag

📅 **Datum**: Wochenende **16.–17. Oktober 2025**

💰 **Vergütung**: 100 € 

👉 **Bewerbung bitte mit**:

📸 Ein paar **aktuelle Fotos**

🎤 Einem kurzen **Vorstellungsvideo** (ca. 30 Sekunden) auf Deutsch

📩 **Bewerbungen und Fragen** bitte per Privatnachricht

## **CASTING VIDÉO – HOMME QUARANTAINE – BIÈRE ARTISANALE**

Vous êtes un homme d’une quarantaine d’années, naturel et à l’aise devant la caméra ?

Vous parlez **allemand couramment** (impératif), et vous pouvez communiquer en **français ou en anglais** avec nos équipes ?

Nous recherchons un figurant pour un tournage publicitaire destiné à la création de **contenus vidéos pour les réseaux sociaux** d’une **marque de bière artisanale**.

📍 **Lieu** : Lausanne, Suisse

🕐 **Durée** : 1 demi-journée de tournage

📅 **Date** : week-end du **16-17 octobre 2025**

💰 **Rémunération** : 100 € 

👉 **Pour candidater, merci d’envoyer** :

📸 Quelques **photos récentes**

🎤 Une courte **vidéo de présentation** (30 sec environ) en allemand

📩 **Candidatures et questions** par message privé

## 
## **VIDEO CASTING – MAN IN HIS 40s – CRAFT BEER**

Are you a man in your 40s, natural and comfortable on camera?

Do you speak **fluent German** (mandatory) and can communicate with our team in **French or English**?

We are looking for a background actor for a commercial shoot to create **video content for the social media channels** of a **craft beer brand**.

📍 **Location**: Lausanne, Switzerland

🕐 **Duration**: Half-day shoot

📅 **Date**: Weekend of **October 16–17, 2025**

💰 **Compensation**: 100 €

👉 **To apply, please send**:

📸 A few **recent photos**

🎤 A short **introduction video** (around 30 seconds) in German

📩 **Applications and questions** via private message

items.text:
**Casting: Models für ein Haarstyling-Fotoshooting 📸**

Hast du Lust, vor der Kamera zu glänzen? Wir suchen Models mit allen Haartypen (lang, kurz, lockig, glatt, natürlich oder gefärbt) für ein kreatives und professionelles Fotoshooting in Berlin.

**Termin und Ort:**
📍 Berlin: **18. und 19. Oktober 2025**

**Projekt-Details:**
* Gage: **120 € pro Stunde**
* Alter: **18 – 35 Jahre**
* Teilnahme: ein oder beide Tage möglich
* Kostenübernahme: Reise- und Unterkunftskosten während des Shootings sind gedeckt

**Bewerbung:**
Bitte sende uns einige Fotos deiner Haare sowie eine kurze Vorstellung an: **manorycasting@gmail.com**

Eine tolle Gelegenheit, Erfahrungen auf einem professionellen Set zu sammeln und dabei Spaß vor der Kamera zu haben!

#CastingBerlin #HairShoot #ModelCasting #Berlin

items.text:
Actors wanted for Dick Whittington, Valley Theatre’s annual seasonal panto.

Audition date and time; 7.15pm, Monday 13th October 2025, at Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Performance dates: Sat 17th Jan 2026(afternoon and eve) and Sun 18th Jan 2026 (afternoon only);

Rehearsal days; Monday 7pm whole cast usually; Thursday eve selected scenes.

Valley Theatre’s traditional panto has become legendary in the area. As a community theatre we pride ourselves on keeping the prices family friendly without compromising on the quality. We like to offer a traditional storyline with well-loved panto routines, popular music, up-to-date and local references, strong on humour.

This is a great opportunity for actors wanting to gain unbeatable stage experience with a friendly and supportive production team.

Wide range of parts available for the experienced and beginner alike. No prep needed for the audition.

Please note: this is non-paying.

More details info@valleytheatre.co.uk

**AUDITION NOTICE FROM PUTNEY THEATRE COMPANY**

**THE SEAFARER**

**by Conor McPherson**
**Sunday 26 October, 3pm**
**Monday 27 October, 7pm***

*If successful, you will be asked to attend a recall on Wednesday 29 October at 7pm

**Performances:**
**Tuesday 17 February 2026 – Saturday 21 February 2026, Putney Arts Theatre **

**AUDITION INFORMATION:**

For the audition you will be asked to perform either a selected monologue or short scene from the play. You may be asked to perform it a second time with some direction or with another auditionee.

All the characters in the play are Irish. All the characters, except for Mr Lockhart, come from Baldoyle, north of Dublin. Mr Lockhart could be from anywhere in Ireland.

When auditioning you should be able to show an ability and familiarity with an Irish accent, although we don’t expect it to be perfect at this point. Unless of course you are from North Dublin!

**Please contact the director on *****[ian@nickhernbooks.co.uk](https://www.putneyartstheatre.org.uk/mailto:%20peterpanto2025@gmail.com)*****  for audition pieces and any further information required.**

**ABOUT THE PLAY:**

A supernatural tale on a dark winter’s evening…

It’s nearly Christmas Eve and Sharky has returned to Dublin to look after his blind brother, Richard. As the two men rattle around their old house, they are joined by local layabouts Ivan and Nicky - and a stranger, new to town, the mysterious Mr Lockhart.

Over a night fuelled by alcohol and resentment, a game of cards is on the table. But the cost of losing may be higher than anyone imagines…

From Conor McPherson, award-winning author of The Weir and Girl from the North Country, comes a blackly funny, haunting tale of family and friendship, steeped in whiskey and stirred by regret and the need for redemption.

**CAST BREAKDOWN:**

Five Men aged 35-65 (ages in brackets are the possible age range for the parts).
* **Sharky**: On the wagon. A man who has lost in life and love but is struggling to be better. Trying to hold it together but lacking in the confidence he once had. (35 - 45)
* **Richard:** A big drinker. Recently blinded. A dishevelled, fetid old rogue. Irascible, childish and demanding but with a whiff of Irish charm. (50 - 65) 
* **Ivan: **A big man. An innocent, but full of anxiety.  A hard drinker who suffers from the aftereffects of his imbibing. (35 - 45)
* **Nicky: **The local wide boy. Confident cocky, always on the up and on the lookout. Thinks he’s much better than he is. (30 - 40)
* **Mr Lockhart:** Enigmatic. A different class to the other men and something of a mystery to them. Sophisticated in comparison, he is possessed of a dark and dangerous edge. (50 - 60)

“Sparkling and suspenseful… McPherson is a born yarn-spinner” Guardian

“A realistic fantasy, a wide-awake nightmare. The writing is poetic, brutal, athletic, hilarious” Sunday Times

“Conor McPherson is the heir to the great Irish tradition of absorbing tale telling” Observer

“The finest dramatist of his generation” The Telegraph 

**Please contact the director on *****[ian@nickhernbooks.co.uk](https://www.putneyartstheatre.org.uk/mailto:%20peterpanto2025@gmail.com)*****  for audition pieces and any further information required.**

**PLEASE NOTE: this is an amateur production and therefore non-paid. **

*FUNDET! 

Jeg søger en hundeejer med en sød familiehund (golden retriever, labrador, den slags, gerne i en lys farve) der kunne have lyst til at have deres hund med i nogle reklamebilleder/film der fremhæver sommerhushygge i Blokhus 😊🦮📷 

Vi laver nemlig nogle optagelser i Blokhus mandag-onsdag, hvor vi gerne vil have nogle scener med en hund. Det drejer sig om et par timer, gerne tirsdag eftermiddag, men andre tidspunkter er også mulige, og det er kun hunden der skal være med. Hunden skal agere sammen med en skuespilsfamilie. 
**Vi har 1500kr til betaling for dette.**

Skriv gerne en kommentar, send mig en besked eller mail på daniel@24copenhagen.dk, hvis du er interesseret.

God søndag!

**CASTINGCALL!!! (Ulønnet)**

Hejsa. vi er i gang med vores andet projekt her på Potemkin, den jyske filmskole - Masterclass. Vi søger derfor skuespillere til Hovedrollen **Alfred**.

Logline: “**Spildt Mælk**” I denne absurde coming-of-age komedie, om identitet, vaner og det at finde sig selv,  møder vi Alfred en ung mand der flytter til storbyen for at starte sit voksenliv. Alt imens hans bizarre afhængighed af mælk vender op og ned på hans nye hverdag og skaber kaos.

**Alfred** (21-25) er en usikker ung gut der lige er flyttet fra landet og ind til storbyen. 

Denne transition er temmelig hård for en så tilbageholdende og usikker dreng som ham, og for at gøre det endnu værre så har han en afhængighed til mælk. Hvordan forklarer man lige sine nye roomies om det? Alfred er godhjertet og ser altid det bedste i folk og vil gerne lære folk at kende, men fordi han er rimelig kejtet så formår han nærmest altid at få et allerede nyt akavet møde til at blive endnu mere akavet.

Optagelserne foregår i Aarhus C den **21. og 22. oktober**. 

der vil være forplejning på set, men jobbet er ulønnet.

vedhæftet dette opslag er scene 01-03 som vi gerne vil se dit bud på i et selftape sendt til min mail. (showreel er velkommen, men vi foretrækker selftape til de valgte scener)

Mvh. Team **Spildt Mælk**. - Potemkin

Bastiankapela@gmail.com

items.text:
We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals –17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer £700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

Please email details including a singing reel to

info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

items.text:
Hi everyone! I'm casting 'All-Round Champion', a CSA & Emmy Award-winning reality sports competition series that brings together 10 of the best youth athletes from across North America and the UK. Each season, these incredible athletes represent 10 different sports and face the ultimate challenge: competing in each other's disciplines for the title of All-Round Champion!

If you know any talented athletes between the ages of 11 and 18 who would thrive in this environment, I'd love for you to share this opportunity with them!

Interested athletes can apply here: [https://allroundchampion7.castingcrane.com](https://allroundchampion7.castingcrane.com/) - please note the deadline for submissions is early November, so don't delay!

Watch our Season 6 trailer to get a feel for the show: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXbmDbRjQ24](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXbmDbRjQ24)

Learn more about our production company: [https://blueantmedia.com/](https://blueantmedia.com/)

Email me your questions at [Jessica.mcgann@blueantmedia.com](mailto:Jessica.mcgann@blueantmedia.com)

items.text:
🎥✨ CASTING CALL – BACKGROUND ROLES ✨🎬

We are looking for actors and actresses of all ages to join us for one-day background roles in our upcoming war drama film “There Are No Children”. Check out our website for more info: https://tancfilm.netlify.app/

📌 Background Roles Needed:
 • Civilians (men, women, children)
 • Wounded civilians & refugees
 • Soldiers
 • Enemy soldiers

🎬 Production Dates:
 • October 25–26 (Principal)
 • November 1–2 (Principal)
 • November 8–9 (Principal)
 • December 6–7 (Pick-ups)

This is a powerful production that explores survival, innocence, and resilience during war. Background performers will help bring authenticity and emotion to the world of the story.

📍 Location: Los Angeles area

Compensation: This is an unpaid student production. Crafty/meals provided on set and film credit will be given.

💌 To apply, please send an email to tancproduction@gmail.com with: 
• your name
• age
• photo
• availability

Join us in bringing this important story to life!

Best Regards,
Iren Tovmasian

UNPAID October 25-26 (Principal) November 1-2 (Principal) November 8-9 (Principal) December 6-7 (Pick-ups) APPLY: tancproduction@gmail com'

Vi søger skuespillere (25–33 år) med anden etnisk herkomst eller afrikaner til en mørk og visuelt ambitiøs musikvideo.

Tre venner finder et sted at overnatte – guidet af en app, der måske lytter lidt for godt.

Det der starter som sjov, bliver hurtigt til noget langt mere foruroligende.

KARAKTERE:

🔹 KAOS – fundet

🔹 BENDER – rolig, men uforudsigelig

🔹 KARMA – drømmende, fanget i sin egen verden

Projektet er ulønnet, men med høj kunstnerisk ambition og stærk visuel stil.

📩 Send headshots + kontaktinfo til elyascaster@gmail.com

Hallo zusammen!

Ich plane einen kurzen Liebes-Drama mit Spannungselementen, bei dem es um Vertrautheit, Gefühle und einen Bösewicht geht. 🌹🖤

Für dieses Projekt suche ich Studenten oder junge Filmemacher, die Lust haben, technisch und kreativ mitzuwirken – sei es Kamera, Ton, Licht oder Produktionssupport. Equipment ist natürlich super, aber genauso wichtig ist Motivation und Spaß am Drehen.

items.text:
# Atem- und Sprechtechnik

Atem- und Sprechtechnik: Entfalte deine volle Ausdruckskraft!

 

Möchtest du:

 

- Klarheit in deiner Stimme erreichen?

- Eine korrekte Aussprache entwickeln?

- Deinen Akzent reduzieren oder akzentfrei sprechen?

- Deinen Dialekteinfluss vermindern?

- Deutlich artikulieren?

- Eine überzeugende Rhetorik beherrschen?

- Frei und selbstbewusst sprechen?

- Verständlich formulieren?

- Wirksam präsentieren?

- Kompetent argumentieren?

- Überzeugend rezitieren (Sachtexte, Prosa, Lyrik, Dramatik usw.)?

- Einfach richtig und gut Deutsch sprechen?

- Ein Medientraining absolvieren?

- Eine Atmung erlernen, die all das ermöglicht?

 

Wenn du nur eine dieser Fragen mit "Ja" beantworten kannst, dann findest du hier alles, was du dafür brauchst.

 

**Und das sagen Teilnehmer*innen (Auswahl):**

Die Testimonials sind aus Datenschutzgründen anonymisiert. Du willst noch mehr Testimonials oder solche, die nicht anonysmisiert sind? Dann lese die Bewertungen auf **[Google](https://www.google.ch/maps/place/ZES+Zentrum+f%C3%BCr+Entwicklung+im+Schauspiel/@47.509748,8.5949863,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x479a9e1995257499:0x6e04509e633044c9!8m2!3d47.509748!4d8.597175)**.

***„Vielen Dank für das Training letzte Woche. Ich habe inzwischen weiter geübt und es fällt mir schon wesentlich leichter mit dem S und fühlt sich natürlicher an.“ R.***

***„Deine Hilfe, Unterstützung und Unterricht gefallen mir sehr. Somit freue ich mich auf die weitere Zusammenarbeit.*** ***Auch ich arbeite sehr gerne mit Dir zusammen.“ T.***

***„Vielen Dank für das ehrliche und konstruktive Feedback!“ K.***

 

Über den Trainer: 

Marco Hausammann-Gilardi bringt mehr als 40 Jahre Erfahrung als Schauspieler, Autor, Regisseur und Produzent in Theater, Film und Fernsehen mit. Er arbeitete zudem als Moderator, Journalist und Redakteur für Radio und Fernsehen, als Sprecher für Werbung, Voice-Over und Synchron (Voice-Artist) und führte Fernseh- und Tonstudioregie.

 

Nutze diese einzigartige Gelegenheit, um deine kommunikativen Fähigkeiten auf das nächste Level zu heben!

 

Der private Unterricht ist persönlich oder via Zoom möglich.

 

Du willst es genau wissen. Auf der Website findest du alles, was du brauchst:

•          Alle Details

•          Testimonials / Bewertungen

•          Die Anmeldung

 

ZES Zentrum für Entwicklung im Schauspiel Zürich

 

[https://zes-info.ch/atem-und-sprechtechnik/](https://zes-info.ch/atem-und-sprechtechnik/)

Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 41/2025

EIN KULTKLASSIKER FEIERT SEINEN 40er UND EIN  LANGFILMCOMEBACK MADE IN AUSTRIA 

Nach 10jähriger Unterbrechung feiert Regisseur Andreas Prochaska mit WELCOME HOME BABY seine Langfilmrückkehr und ist bei uns im Interview zu hören.

Vor 43 Jahren startete das Franchise und kehrt mit TRON: ARES aktuell in die Kino zurück.

Die letzten Kriegstage des 2. WK auf einer Insel in Deutschland erzählt uns sensibel AMRUM von Regisseur Fatih Akin, der uns ein paar Worte spendete. 

Ausserdem feiert der Fluxkompensator einen runden Geburtstag. 

Abgerundet mit weiteren Film Highlights und Musik aus Filmen der letzten 80 Jahre begleitet Sie Sarah Fuchs durch die Sendung. 

Mittwoch 8.10.25 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 1st week in November 2025 (date tbc). For actors based in the London area.

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  25-35, 5’ 6”+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of £300 for 15 hours. 

BACKGROUND MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 25-35, 5’ 6”+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for £150 for 7 hours. 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

items.title: CASTING CALL

items.text:
📣🎬 Casting Call – Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‘A Race with Ian Hitchworth’, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:�Ian Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again—culminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian’s arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)�25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he’s arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously — but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)�Any age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)�18–40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025�To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Needs strong comedic timing, improvisational skills, and comfort with physical comedy. Interviewer (Supporting) Dry, deadpan delivery. Provides calm contrast to lan's chaotic Race Official/ Athletes (Supporting & Extras) 18-40, any gender. Includes race official and background runners. Must look on track. dates Seeking contributors voluntarily travel expenses and food will be provided. Toapply send headshots &CV'sto'

CASTING CALL - FEMALE HAIR CARE BRAND SOCIAL MEDIA VIDEOS

We are looking for a female influencer/actor/model as specified below:

Shoot Date: 15th OR 16th October

Location: London (TBC on precise location)

Hours: 1.5 hours work

Paid £150 plus travel expenses

Must be based in London/Greater London

Must be comfortable getting their hair wet and using Goldwell products

If interested, please contact us on email only goldwellcreators@wearemonty.com with your spotlight page or any other relevant promotional materials. Thank you!

The ideal candidate should be comfortable filming trends. It will be a 1.5 hour shoot on the 15th OR 16th October at studio space in London. (TBC on precise location and timings, so please let us know your availability) ATTRIBUTES Gender: Female, Age: 20s-30s Appearance: Healthy, well styled hair'

THE SUMMONED is a terrifying, edge of your seat, horror play, which takes you on a journey through a ritual gone wrong at an abandoned monastery.

JUST TWO WEEKS TO GO!!! THE ETCETERA THEATRE RUN IS ALMOST SOLD OUT BUT CATCH THE SHOW AT THE LION & UNICORN WHILE TICKETS ARE STILL AVAILABLE!!

Aside from setting your heart racing, and making you doubt everything you think you know, THE SUMMONED is a story of love, loss, friendship, grief and humanity.

We guarantee you have NEVER seen anything like this in the theatre.

items.text:
My name is Luke Kenyon, and I’m a film student at SAE Liverpool. We’re currently working on a new short film project titled Last Night and are looking to cast two male-identifying actors (mid twenties)to join our team. This project is Non paid but we will be providing travel expenses as well as catering 

Synopsis -

On the anniversary of his best friend’s suicide, Aaron plans to end his own life. He ignores his mothers phone calls and edges closer towards his own end, until he unexpectedly hears a knock at his apartment front door. His best friend, Ben, appears in an attempt to make amends and guide Aaron away from darkness. This intimate drama, through one final, raw conversation, forces Aaron to choose between following the same path that Ben took a year ago, or answering the call that could save him.

Aaron:

Aaron, mid 20's, slightly introverted and reserved. A complicated character with a lot going on in his mind. His low confidence makes it hard for him to open up to others about his feelings, especially about the loss of his best friend (Ben), who meant the world to him. He loves music and even used to play in a band with Ben. 

Ben:

Ben, mid 20's, soft and sensitive personality. His battles with his own mental health has led him to an unfortunate end, which ultimately, has hurt someone very close to him (Aaron), although this was never his intention. Ben’s aim is to make some sort of amends from his past actions and to help Aaron not make the same mistake that he did. 

If you have any questions about the project or roles, please don’t hesitate to get in touch — I’m happy to provide more information.

If you  are interested in applying, please use one of the provided links below or alternatively email me at 120206uk@saeinstitute.edu with your details, previous work, or portfolio. (Including heat shots) please provide which role you are applying for 

Thank you very much for your time We look forward to hearing from you!

Kind regards,

Luke Kenyon

Film Student, SAE Institute

https://www.backstage.com/casting/last-night-student-film-3019197/

https://www.starnow.com/casting/last-night-3021254/

https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3021242/last-night/

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‘ Habeus Corpus’ by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett’s Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the ﬂat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Sir Percy Shorter - chairman of the BMA, quite upper class and not too tall (Mid 40s+

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall

Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 

Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.

Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 

The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information, contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

items.text:
🎀 Legally Blonde – de musical 🎀

Na succesvolle producties zoals The Prom, Aida, Beauty and the Beast, Ghost en Evita, brengen wij in september 2026 een frisse, energieke en hilarische voorstelling van Legally Blonde.

We zijn op zoek naar nieuw talent vanaf 15 jaar

Zin om mee te zingen, spelen en dansen in een van de leukste feelgoodmusicals ooit? Dan is dit je kans!

📍 Locatie: Knokke-Heist

🎭 Organisatie: Musicalgroep MILO (www.musicalgroepmilo.be)

📅 Voorstellingen: september 2026

🎤 Audities & repetities: vinden plaats in Knokke-Heist

👉 Inschrijven voor de auditie:

www.musicalgroepmilo.be

De plaatsen voor auditie zijn beperkt, dus snel inschrijven is aangeraden!

LEGALLY BLONDE de Musical!

Elle Woods lijkt het perfecte leven te hebben — roze outfits, een charmante vriend en eindeloze good vibes.

Maar wanneer haar grote liefde haar dumpt omdat ze “niet serieus genoeg” is, besluit Elle hem achterna te gaan… naar Harvard Law School.

Wat begint als een romantisch plan, groeit uit tot een verhaal vol humor, lef en zelfvertrouwen — waarin Elle bewijst dat je met stijl én brains alles kunt bereiken!

Of je nu houdt van comedy, zang, krachtige ensemblemomenten of gewoon helemaal losgaat op dans — voor elk wat wils!

Dus trek je mooiste outfit aan (roze optioneel ), warm je stem óf spieren op en schrijf je in voor de audities van LEGALLY BLONDE!

#LegallyBlonde #Audities #MusicalgroepMILO #JoinTheFun #MusicalVibes #TheatreMagic #pinkpower

Na succesvolle producties zoals The Prom, Aida, Beauty and the Beast, Ghost en Evita, brengen wij in september 2026 een frisse, energieke en hilarische voorstelling van Legally Blonde.

We zijn op zoek naar nieuw talent vanaf 15 jaar

Zin om mee te zingen, spelen en dansen in een van de leukste feelgoodmusicals ooit? Dan is dit je kans!

📍 Locatie: Knokke-Heist

🎭 Organisatie: Musicalgroep MILO (www.musicalgroepmilo.be)

📅 Voorstellingen: september 2026

🎤 Audities & repetities: vinden plaats in Knokke-Heist

👉 Inschrijven voor de auditie:

www.musicalgroepmilo.be

De plaatsen voor auditie zijn beperkt, dus snel inschrijven is aangeraden!

LEGALLY BLONDE de Musical!

Elle Woods lijkt het perfecte leven te hebben — roze outfits, een charmante vriend en eindeloze good vibes.

Maar wanneer haar grote liefde haar dumpt omdat ze “niet serieus genoeg” is, besluit Elle hem achterna te gaan… naar Harvard Law School.

Wat begint als een romantisch plan, groeit uit tot een verhaal vol humor, lef en zelfvertrouwen — waarin Elle bewijst dat je met stijl én brains alles kunt bereiken!

Of je nu houdt van comedy, zang, krachtige ensemblemomenten of gewoon helemaal losgaat op dans — voor elk wat wils!

Dus trek je mooiste outfit aan (roze optioneel ), warm je stem óf spieren op en schrijf je in voor de audities van LEGALLY BLONDE!

#LegallyBlonde #Audities #MusicalgroepMILO #JoinTheFun #MusicalVibes #TheatreMagic #pinkpower

items.text:
(Kraków) Szukam ludzi do spektaklu historyczno-poetyckiego, w stylu filmowym, epickim, opartym na życiorysach Tadeusza Borowskiego i Krzysztofa Kamila Baczyńskiego. Premiera przewidziana jest na marzec 2026 roku. Potrzebuję ludzi czujących epokę, poezję, niekoniecznie zawodowców. Poniżej lista postaci, do których szukam aktorów:
* Tadeusz (postać główna, pierwowzór - Tadeusz Borowski i Wincenty Gawron)
* Krzysztof (pierwowzór - K. K. Baczyński)
* Stary Doktor (pierwowzór - Janusz Korczak)
* Kapelan (pierwowzów - ksiądz Tiso)
* Bracia żydowscy Jakub i Izaak
* Roma (żona polskiego oficera)
* Pola (pierwowzór - Barbara Baczyńska)
* Rachela (żydowska dziewczyna, wieszczka, pieśniarka)
* ''Święta'' (handlująca zrabowanymi kosztownościami)
* oficerowie hitlerowscy - Wolf i Jurgen

Chętne osoby zapraszam do kontaktu na priv. Pozdrawiam.

items.text:
**WARSZAWA 11 października**

**film fabularny - Rola Epizodyczna**

**Stawka: 1000 zł**

Do roli epizodycznej w filmie fabularnym JAN BO szukam młodej atrakcyjnej kobiety, która wystąpi w scenie - **topless**.

Bez kontrowersji. Jeden z bohaterów budzi się obok pięknej dziewczyny. Jest do połowy przykryta.

**Do zgłoszenia proszę załączyć wizytówkę jako link do YouTube.**

Ponieważ gramy lata 80te mamy nieuniknione wytyczne charakteryzacji:
* brak tatuaży 
* bez tuneli w uszach, kolczyków w wardze, nosie czy brwiach
* paznokcie TYLKO naturalne.
* bez permanentnych makijaży, doklejonych rzęs i  ingerencji medycyny estetycznej

**ZGŁOSZENIA**

Poproszę na adres: **ewelina.wika@podtytulem.pl**

W tytule: **GIRL**

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość + wymiary: wzrost, klatka, pas, biodra, rozmiar ubrania i buta + wizytówka

W załączniku: ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI (ubrane): tylko z dnia zgłoszenia.
* Portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy.
* Bez makijażu, w rozpuszczonych włosach tak, żeby widoczna była długość włosów

Model • Performer • TV-Erfahrung

Ich stehe noch am Anfang aber ich liebe, Ausdruck und Wandelbarkeit – vor der Kamera, auf der Bühne und in jeder Produktion. Mit Pole Dance und Tanz vereine ich Eleganz, Stärke und kreative Energie. Jede Bewegung, jeder Look erzählt eine Geschichte – von sinnlich bis kraftvoll.

Instagram:Jx.anie

Meine TV-Auftritte als Komparse (Berlin – Tag & Nacht, Anwälte im Einsatz, Auf Streife) haben mir zusätzliche Präsenz und Kamera-Sicherheit gegeben. Für Fashion, Beauty, Werbung & kreative Kooperationen bringe ich Professionalität, Leidenschaft und Persönlichkeit mit.

Dates

Playing dates 1st-23rd December 
We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.
We are offering 700 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required. 
MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

items.text:
The Brookside Theatre, Romford is urgently looking for a male actor (playing age 45-60) for their Halloween production; THE ADDAMS FAMILY 

Role: Mal Beineke (Actor with good comic timing. Does need to sing a few lines but these are character vocals)
Accent: US (General or NYC)

Sadly due to an injury and subsequent surgery, the actor playing role has had to withdraw

Rehearsals: Weekday evenings and Sunday daytimes (some flexibility)

Show dates: 29th Oct - 2nd Nov 2025

Venue: Brookside Theatre, Romford (2 mins walk from Elizabeth Line Station / Free Parking)

Unpaid charity production

If you think you can step in and save the show then please get in touch asap - email casting@brooksidetheatre.com or PM me

Keeping everything crossed as we really don't want to cancel

#castingcall #casting #addamsfamilymusical #musicaltheatre #stage #stageshow

items.text:
ROSTER CALL: ICT Productions (SAG-AFTRA & DGA Signatory)

My company, ICT Productions, is building a first-call roster across departments for upcoming narrative, branded, and live projects in Los Angeles.

We’re an award-winning company and I’ve personally managed $200M+ across network/broadcast productions (including the Super Bowl) and multiple films in active development.

This is not an invite for immediate work; it’s an invite to join our vetted roster we call before any public search.

Departments (all levels welcome):

Production (Producers, UPM/PM, Coordinators)
AD Dept
Script Supervisor
Camera
G&E
Sound
Art/Set Dec
Props
Construction/Scenic
Wardrobe
Hair/Makeup
Locations
Stunts/Intimacy
SFX
Medics/Safety
Transportation
Video/DIT
VFX
Post (Editorial/Color/Sound/Score)
EPK/BTS
Crafty/Catering
Security

Email: jake@ictproductions.com

Subject: ICT Roster - [NAME]

• Role(s) + union status
• Base day rate + kit notes (if any)
• IMDb / Reel / Portfolio
• Home-base ZIP
• Best contact info
• Note if open to student/ultra-low projects

We run professional, safety-first, union-aligned sets with clear paperwork and on-time pay. 

Equal opportunity; all backgrounds encouraged to submit.

Thanks! Looking forward to meeting you.

Jake Crossman, Producer
ICT Productions, Los Angeles, CA
(747) 528-7818
jake@ictproductions.com

items.text:
CASTING CALL 

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production 

Project Type: UCF BFA Short Film 

Union Status: Non-Union 

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected 

Shooting Dates: TBD 

Shooting Location: Orlando area 

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her. 

This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production. 

Character Breakdowns: 

MONOMAY: Female, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants.

Hej alle, 

Vi søger 3 statister til vores kortfilm FLYT DIG i alderen 60-100, køn er underordnet.

En konfliktsky ung mand bliver udnyttet af sine venner og ignoreret af sin familie. Da hans rebelske fætter hjælper ham med at flytte, må han indse, at frihed ikke bare handler om at bryde ud – men om at turde definere sine egne grænser.

Optagelserne foregår i tilst tirsdag d. 14 oktober fra 9-17. Der vil være forplejninger på set.

Skriv til mig på messenger eller til *sara774g@gmail.com* ved interesse.

Venlig Hilsen, Sara Riahi

items.text:
**CASTING CALL – LONDON (November–December)**

Hi Everyone,

I’m Ben, a founder trying to do something a bit mad in the run-up to Christmas.

I’ve made a new family game and have **5,000 boxes to sell before Christmas**… or I have to be a normal adult and go back to being an accountant again! 

We’re filming the real journey: street pitches, rejections, laughs, and small wins, all turned into short daily LinkedIn episodes (1–3 minutes each). Think *founder documentary meets chaos comedy*.

I’m looking for a few actors to jump in and help out, people who can play along naturally as friends, supporters, or street crew in different moments of the campaign.

**Location:** London

**When:** November–December (run-up to Christmas)

**Paid freelance role:** Not a massive budget, but there is a budget.

**Commitment:** Half a day, 1 day a week for 4 weeks. Need 5 actors, one for each day of the week.

**Who suits this:**
* Chatty, funny, naturally comfortable on camera
* Up for improvising and rolling with the madness
* Down-to-earth, good energy, friendly vibe

If you’re **fun, talented, and up for helping make a tabletop game go viral**, drop me a DM with a short intro or clip.

Ben

items.text:
SYGEPLEJESKOLEN sæson 8 - HONORAR 700 KR.

Fredag d. 10. oktober kl. 9.30 - 13.30 i Risby ved Albertslund 

Honorar 700 kr

Der er gratis parkering, og der er forplejning tilpasset tidsrum.

Udgifter til f.eks. transport refunderes ikke.

Til mandlig statistrolle som ambulanceredder søges mand med erfaring med at køre bårer.

KOSTUMEKRAV: skjorte 40 og jakke str. 48. 

Dette er vigtigt, du er sikker på din str., da kostumet skal passe.

ANDRE KRAV PGA. TIDSPERIODEN:

Hårlængde korthåret - max hårlængde ned over ørerne, du kan blive trimmet af frisør på produktionen, ingen kronraget eller karseklippet, ensfarvet hår med mindre gråt.

Ingen skæg. Du skal kunne møde op glatbarberet.

Ingen synlige tatoveringer med kortærmet bluse på, ingen synlige piercinger.

Tjek gerne pressefotos fra Sygeplejeskolens øvrige sæsoner, så du kan se, om din hårlænge er et match.

I 1950erne var Danmark ikke beriget med mange forskellige etniske herkomster, så jeg kan desværre kun caste statister, som den danske befolkning så ud dengang.

Send en mail til ajlystbaek@hotmail.com med emne ambulanceredder.

Jeg skal have oplyst navn, alder, mobilnummer, højde, bluse str., jakke str., bukse str., sko str. og vedhæft kun 1 helt nyt billede af dig i helfigur max 1 MB.

1 billede på MAX 1 MB.

Dit ansigt, hår inkl. længde og krop skal kunne ses tydeligt. Du skal stå alene på billedet. Der må ikke bruges filter på billedet, så vi kan se dig, som du ser ud.

Hello! We are shooting an unpaid improvised short film next week from the 15th to the 18th of October based on the concept for our feature film SOPHIE, and we are looking for an actor for one for the lead roles, to play a charismatic pubcrawl guide (25-35, Male) with a dark side. Shooting will take place on the 15th, 16th, 17th and 18th of October, all night shoots.

If you're interested in knowing more details please send me your showreel or a short introductory video of you and your acting experience, to vasco.cinema.2018@gmail.com.

Sinopsis: On a weekend escape to Copenhagen, Sophie reunites with an old friend and spirals through a night of fleeting connections, as she’s forced to confront the cost of trying to feel anything at all.

items.text:
Actors (non-union) needed for a documentary regarding Elizabeth Johnson Jr who was the last convicted witch to be exonerated from the 1692 Salem Witchcraft Trials.

The ideal actor for Elizabeth will have strawberry blond or slight red hair, be of average height and able to portray early 20s.

Two additional actors will be needed as elders (40-60) who arrest her and walk her away.

The shoot will require one day in early November or early December on north of Boston. Pay will be negotiated.  Access to a late 17th century costume is a plus. Send headshot, resume and November, December availability to SalemHistoricalTours@gmail.com

items.text:
Stirling Players are looking for an actor to fill the role of the identical Gray twins, in its final production for the year, Making a Meal Of It. The Gray twins, Albert and Alfred are a couple of standover villains. The actor can be any age between 25 and 65.
The season runs November 21 to December 6. Rehearsals are Tuesday and Thursday evenings and Sunday afternoons, at Stirling Theatre in Innaloo. The Grays character wouldn't be required for every rehearsal as it is a minor role. If you are interested, please call the director, Bob Charteris on 045036582, or email him at charterisfamily@hotmail.com

items.text:
MY MOMMA’S ERA: THE MUSICAL – SEEN THROUGH MY MOTHER’S LENS

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater – 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(It’s recommended — not required — for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzeville’s rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago — told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicago’s own.

A dynamic cast. Real stories. Legendary music.
This is more than entertainment — it’s edutainment.

TICKETS & GROUP BENEFITS
Group rates (10+) already discounted online
Call 773-655-3575 for Senior & Youth group discounts!

Eventbrite (Use code: MyMommasEra2025):
 https://www.eventbrite.com/e/my-mommas-era-the-musical-stage-play-tickets-1302271441939?aff=oddtdtcreator

Zeffy (No fees to us!):
 https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/ticketing/my-mommas-era-the-musical-stage-play

 SUPPORT THE MOVEMENT – DONATE TODAY
Dream Real Theatre Company is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit using the arts to educate, inspire, and transform.

Zeffy (tax-deductible):
https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/donation-form/donate-to-make-a-difference-19332

 PayPal:
https://www.paypal.com/donate?hosted_button_id=4HEYR2LBTP8J8

Zelle: 773-655-3575 

“We will not hide them from their children, but tell to the coming generation the glorious deeds of the Lord…” – Psalm 78:4

Tag a friend, post your outfit inspo, and share the legacy!
Subscribe on YouTube: @dreamrealtheatrecompany2270

#MyMommasEra #DreamRealTheatre #ChicagoTheatre #LiveStage #MusicalHistory #BlackLegacy #Bronzeville #MinnieRiperton #Edutainment #SupportTheArts #40sFashion #50sStyle #60sSoul #70sVibes #RegalTheatre #JukeJoints #NonprofitArts

items.text: One of my first short films from 2023 🎥 “Asher Knows”

sharedPost.text:
🎬 Asher Knows
After his father’s sudden death, a young man trapped in a dead-end job is forced into the criminal world his father left behind—but as his choices destroy the people he loves, he must fight to break free and rebuild his life before he’s lost to the same cycle forever.

 A drama short film written and directed by Antoñía Maritza Amp.
Starring: Natalio Seven McGuffie, “Dew” Craig Dewberry, Ro Marcano, Buddy Rowe, Mary Jerome, Romeo & Chad Marcano. FIlmed in June 2023.

🎵 Music Credits 🎵
“Jook” – Bobby Ray Postell
“Litty (Weekend)” – Afterse7en
“Only the Real Ones” (feat. Burga) – 6CO
“Homie Don’t Like Me” – Buddy Rowe
“2 Milly” – Jabba
“Brand New Drip” – Burga
“Nasty” – Grindhard & Dew
“Lifestyle” – YNW Smokedaloc
“Get Thee” (feat. Destiny) – Zion’s Garden 

Special thanks to Lizzys Restaurant and Carabella Wellness Spa for opening their doors and allowing us to film in their spaces.

RIP Craig "Dew" Dewberry 💙💛

items.text:
MY MOMMA’S ERA: THE MUSICAL – SEEN THROUGH MY MOTHER’S LENS

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater – 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(It’s recommended — not required — for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzeville’s rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago — told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicago’s own.

A dynamic cast. Real stories. Legendary music.
This is more than entertainment — it’s edutainment.

TICKETS & GROUP BENEFITS
Group rates (10+) already discounted online
Call 773-655-3575 for Senior & Youth group discounts!

Eventbrite (Use code: MyMommasEra2025):
 https://www.eventbrite.com/e/my-mommas-era-the-musical-stage-play-tickets-1302271441939?aff=oddtdtcreator

Zeffy (No fees to us!):
 https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/ticketing/my-mommas-era-the-musical-stage-play

 SUPPORT THE MOVEMENT – DONATE TODAY
Dream Real Theatre Company is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit using the arts to educate, inspire, and transform.

items.summary:
MY MOMMA’S ERA: THE MUSICAL – SEEN THROUGH MY MOTHER’S LENS

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater – 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(It’s recommended — not required — for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzeville’s rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago — told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicago’s own.

A dynamic cast. Real stories. Legendary music.
This is more than entertainment — it’s edutainment.

TICKETS & GROUP BENEFITS
Group rates (10+) already discounted online
Call 773-655-3575 for Senior & Youth group discounts!

Eventbrite (Use code: MyMommasEra2025):
 https://www.eventbrite.com/e/my-mommas-era-the-musical-stage-play-tickets-1302271441939?aff=oddtdtcreator

Zeffy (No fees to us!):
 https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/ticketing/my-mommas-era-the-musical-stage-play

 SUPPORT THE MOVEMENT – DONATE TODAY
Dream Real Theatre Company is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit using the arts to educate, inspire, and transform.

Zeffy (tax-deductible):
https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/donation-form/donate-to-make-a-difference-19332

 PayPal:
https://www.paypal.com/donate?hosted_button_id=4HEYR2LBTP8J8

Zelle: 773-655-3575 

“We will not hide them from their children, but tell to the coming generation the glorious deeds of the Lord…” – Psalm 78:4

Tag a friend, post your outfit inspo, and share the legacy!
Subscribe on YouTube: @dreamrealtheatrecompany2270

#MyMommasEra #DreamRealTheatre #ChicagoTheatre #LiveStage #MusicalHistory #BlackLegacy #Bronzeville #MinnieRiperton #Edutainment #SupportTheArts #40sFashion #50sStyle #60sSoul #70sVibes #RegalTheatre #JukeJoints #NonprofitArts

items.text:
**SHORT FILM CREW CALL -***** Beyond the Blue Light***

*ISO of lgbtq, bipoc, and immigrant filmmakers to fill the following positions. All details below. Students welcome!*

*PAID:*

Studio Teacher (one minor 8 or 9 years old)

*IMDB Credit, Copy, Meals, Gas Stipend:*

2nd AC

Key Grip 

G&E Swing

Costumer (+ materials stipend)

Boom OP

PA

**Synopsis:**

*Beyond the Blue Light* is an emotionally charged drama about the cost of apathy in the chronically online era told through the perspective of two trans latine immigrants. 

**Location:**

Los Angeles: Hollywood & North Hollywood

**Dates:**

11/1 - 11/4

**About the Director:**

Simone Brazzini is an award winning filmmaker from Lima, Peru and now based in Los Angeles. Their debut LA short will be making its world premiere at the Micheaux Film Festival. They were recently named in a Deadline article and is a Soho House x Creative Futures Mentee. Simone founded Vibes Video in 2021, a production company that creates radically authentic work across all genres with a focus on lgbtq, bipoc, and neurodiverse voices on and off camera. 

**To Submit:**

Please email a portfolio and/or resume to vibesvideoproductions@gmail.com AND CC productions.fakeid@gmail.com

**THANK YOU**

items.text:
Seeking actors to come and be in my film this Saturday 11th October from 10-12.30. 

It's a very fast shoot. The premise is a very simple group portrait, where I direct from behind the camera to express certain emotional states. No preparation needed. 

The filming will take place in my studio in Bermondsey, London SE1. 

I don't have funds to pay but you can have the footage for whatever you need (reel etc) and I will provide refreshments. 

Looking for 10-20 actors. 

Please email me with interest!

angelzinovieff@gmail.com

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 1st week in November 2025 (date tbc). For actors based in the London area.

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  25-35, 5’ 6”+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of £300 for 15 hours. 

BACKGROUND MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 25-35, 5’ 6”+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for £150 for 7 hours. 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

topComments.text: I sent an email 5th of September with no response?

Teatergruppen Fabulas inviterer hermed alle dygtige skuespillere til audition på vores kommende opsætning “DET’ EN KRIMI”, der er en nyskrevet og interaktiv krimi-komedie, hvor publikum er med til at opklare, hvem der er morderen 🕵️

Vi spiller på Randers Teater i uge 23 og 24 i 2026 ❤

I kan læse meget mere om rollerne og audtionen inde i begivenhederne 🤩

**Vær obs. på at vi holder audition over 2 dage**

Vi håber at se jer 🥳

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 1st week in November 2025 (date tbc). For actors based in the London area.

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  25-35, 5’ 6”+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of £300 for 15 hours. 

BACKGROUND MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 25-35, 5’ 6”+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for £150 for 7 hours. 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

items.text:
**Casting Calls - Standard Posting Format**

***CU Denver Student Film Casting Call***

Title: **Wolf Tickets**

Genre: Drama, True Crime

**Logline:** A florist becomes convinced that her boyfriend, an ex-felon, poses a deadly threat to her and her unborn child, sparking a Rashomon-style tale of paranoia, alienation, and tragedy.

**Synopsis:** A pregnant woman, Vivienne, is murdered by her lover, Anthony, an ex-con with a dark past. Through two distinct narratives, it is revealed how this tragedy came to be. Vivienne’s perspective reveals how fear and miscommunication can distort our perceptions; over the course of two months, we see Antony quickly becoming the monster that he once was. Meanwhile, Antony’s story exposes the devastating consequences of alienation and desperation

Main Roles: 

**Vivienne: **Vivienne is the protagonist of Wolf Tickets. A brown, female, florist in her early 30s. She fits the “broken optimist archetype. In her past, she had a brief fling with her employee, Anthony, an ex-convict. After experiencing a major epiphany stemming from the news that she’s pregnant, she begins to distance herself from Anthony - the result is catastrophic and leads to her eventual death.

**Anthony: **Anthony is the antagonist of Wolf Tickets. A male ex-convict in his early 30s is employed at a flower shop. He fits the “dreamer bound by reality” archetype. Anthony exudes charm but struggles to adapt to life outside of prison, finding solace in his relationship with Vivienne. After parting ways with her, Anthony begins to feel increasingly isolated and lost. With no clear direction or confidence, he’s suddenly overcome with the urge to repeat his past mistakes.

Writer/Director: Daniel Moreno

Producer: Emily Ball

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: For more information or questions prior to auditions, please email Emily at tvdinnerstudios25@gmail.com

Run Time: 8 Minute Short Film

Compensation: Unpaid

Additional Compensation: Meals Provided, Film Credit, & Copy of Final Cut 

Union Status: Non-Union

**Audition Information:**
* Submit a Self-tape to the Google Form Linked Below by October 9th
* Callbacks: TBD
   * They will be held at the CU Denver Campus 

Please fill out this Google Form if you wish to audition

[[https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSegEF6rOSLKsuxeipIXUZYTcGrluRFoBeceC9YKOoSSIMwo4w/viewform?usp=header](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSegEF6rOSLKsuxeipIXUZYTcGrluRFoBeceC9YKOoSSIMwo4w/viewform?usp=header)](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSegEF6rOSLKsuxeipIXUZYTcGrluRFoBeceC9YKOoSSIMwo4w/viewform?usp=header)

**Shooting Schedule:** October. 25th - October 27th & November 16th/17th (Times TBD)

**Filming Location:**
* Arvada, CO.
* Denver, CO.
* Westminster, CO.

Link to Sides: [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1CtgTTGsdSs-B6wew23imvIFsoH_ILsas/view?usp=sharing](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1CtgTTGsdSs-B6wew23imvIFsoH_ILsas/view?usp=sharing)
